                                   A BILL

To govern the transition of United States alliance commitments from a posture
of automatic primacy to one of federated mutual security consistent with the
commons infrastructure established by the Federal Resilience and
Decentralization Initiatives Act; to renegotiate the terms of American
participation in the North Atlantic Treaty Organization and related security
arrangements on a resilience-based and commons-consistent foundation; to
establish a nuclear nonproliferation posture oriented toward multilateral
disarmament; to reform American participation in multilateral economic
institutions whose structural conditions are inconsistent with commons
institution development; to provide for international commons solidarity
through the recognition and support of commons institutions abroad; and to
encode, through the deliberate non-proliferation of extractive economic
arrangements, the conditions for a transition to a provisioned and
ecologically sustainable international order.

Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives of the United States
of America in Congress assembled,

